00:14:18.265 --> 00:14:24.463
multiply matrices,
and how to write linear systems

00:14:24.463 --> 00:14:28.558
in matrix form.
So, remember,

00:14:28.558 --> 00:14:35.970
if you have a 3x3 linear system
in the usual sense,

00:14:35.970 --> 00:14:42.538
so, 
you can write this in a matrix

00:14:42.538 --> 00:14:52.373
form where you have a 3x3 matrix
and you have an unknown column

00:14:52.373 --> 00:14:57.099
vector.
And, their matrix product

00:14:57.099 --> 00:15:01.620
should be some given column
vector.

00:15:01.620 --> 00:15:04.737
OK, so if you don't remember
