here,

00:24:00.630 --> 00:24:03.390
one line here,
and one line there.

00:24:03.390 --> 00:24:06.579
And, there's no triple
intersection.

00:24:06.579 --> 00:24:08.859
So, in general,
we haven't really seen how to

00:24:08.859 --> 00:24:13.765
decide between these two cases.
There's one important situation

00:24:13.765 --> 00:24:20.362
where we have seen we must be in
the first case that when we have

00:24:20.362 --> 00:24:26.161
a homogeneous system,
so that means if the right hand

00:24:26.161 --> 00:24:31.029
side is zero,
then, 

00:24:31.029 --> 00:24:41.750
well, x equals zero is always a
solution.

00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:43.539
It's called the trivial
solution.

00:24:43.539 --> 00:24:50.170
It's the obvious one,
if you want.

00:24:50.170 --> 00:24:53.210
So, you know that,
and why is that?

00:24:53.210 --> 00:24:57.225
Well, that's because all of
your planes have to pass through

00:24:57.225 --> 00:25:00.162
the origin.
So, you must be in this case if

00:25:00.162 --> 00:25:04.070
you have a noninvertible system
where the right hand side is

00:25:04.070 --> 00:25:05.667
zero.
So, in that case,

00:25:05.667 --> 00:25:08.870
if the right hand side is zero,
there's two cases.

00:25:08.870 --> 00:25:12.305
Either the matrix is invertible.
Then, the only solution is the

00:25:12.305 --> 00:25:14.885
trivial one.
Or, if a matrix is not

00:25:14.885 --> 00:25:19.329
invertible, then you have
infinitely many solutions.

00:25:19.329 --> 00:25:23.922
If B is not zero,
